ca.uqac.lif.labpal

Class Laboratory

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.labpal.Laboratory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.OwnershipManager

    public abstract class Laboratory
extends Object
implements ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.OwnershipManager
    A set of experiments, tables and plots. The lab is controlled by a lab assistant, which is responsible for running the experiments, populating the tables and drawing the plots.
    Author:
    Sylvain Hall√©

      • isEnvironmentOk

        public String isEnvironmentOk()
        Checks whether the environment for running the experiments in this lab is appropriate. Override this method if you want to check that some general conditions on the environment are met (such as: presence of some executable in the path, existence of a network connection, etc.).

        As a rule, returning false means that something external to the lab must be fixed before running the experiments; hence ParkBench will simply quit. If your experiments have prerequisites they can generate, don't use this method.

        Returns:
        null if the tests can be run, a String with an explanation otherwise.

      • setupCli

        public void setupCli(CliParser parser)
        Sets up the command-line parser to accept arguments specific to this lab. Your lab should override this method if you wish to receive custom CLI arguments. In such a case, call the methods on the parser variable to add new command-line switches.
        Parameters:
        parser - The command-line parser

      • setup

        public abstract void setup()
        Sets up the experiments and plots that this lab will contain. You must implement this method and add at least one experiment (otherwise there won't be anything to do with your lab).

      • setupCallbacks

        public void setupCallbacks(List<WebCallback> callbacks)
        Sets the custom callbacks to the web server. This allows a lab to include custom pages in its web interface.
        Parameters:
        callbacks - An empty list. The method should add new callbacks to this list. These callbacks will be added to the server if the --web option is used at startup.

      • getCliArguments

        public final CliParser.ArgumentMap getCliArguments()
        Gets the command-line arguments parsed when launching this lab.
        Returns:
        A map of arguments and values parsed from the command line. If you specified custom command-line arguments in setupCli(CliParser), this is where you can retrieve them and read their values.

      • countParkMips

        public static float countParkMips()
        Counts the number of "parkmips" of this system. This is a very rough indicator of the system's speed, measured in the number of increments of a long variable during a third of a second.

        ParkMips are designed to equal roughly 1 when run on an Asus Transformer Book T200 (yes, this is totally arbitrary).

        Returns:
        The number of parkmips

      • getDescription

        public final String getDescription()
        Gets the lab's textual description. This description is either the text given in a previous call to setDescription(String), or, if no such call was made, the contents of a file called description.html that resides beside the lab. If no such file exists, the empty string is returned.
